# .NET build output
[Bb]in/
[Oo]bj/
[Oo]ut/

# Exception: the npm shim at npm/bin/mssql-mcp must be committed.
# The general [Bb]in/ rule above matches the npm/bin/ directory; re-include it
# and the shim file explicitly. Git cannot re-include a file if its parent
# directory is ignored, so we negate both.
# The committed file is a Node.js shim. The postinstall script (npm/install.js)
# overwrites it with the real native binary. Developers who run `npm install`
# locally will see it modified in git status — restore with
# `git checkout -- npm/bin/mssql-mcp`. See ADR-0002 (sqz pattern) and ADR-0014.
!npm/bin/
!npm/bin/mssql-mcp

